Yes, you need to make another fetch request for the languages_url endpoint. Alternatively, you can use GraphQL to get the languages of a repository in a single request. See below code for the GraphQL call. Ref. [GraphQL][1]

    {
      repository(owner: &quot;&lt;&lt;OWNER&gt;&gt;&quot;, name: &quot;&lt;&lt;REPONAME&gt;&gt;&quot;) {
        name
        languages(first: 10) {
          edges {
            node {
              name
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }


  [1]: https://developer.github.com/v4/guides/

