The issue here is that you are creating two separate calls that don&#39;t connect.

Instead of generating two calls using the REST API, you need to return [TwiML][1] from the URI in your URI parameter that connects the call to the person to the Watson agent. So you should set the URI in your `callPhone` method to a URL in your own application. And that URI should return TwiML that includes [`&lt;Dial&gt;`][2] to connect to the agent in this case using [`&lt;Sip&gt;`][3].

The TwiML should look a bit like this:

```xml
&lt;Response&gt;
  &lt;Dial&gt;
    &lt;Sip&gt;sip:TwilioPhoneNumber@us-south.voiceagent.cloud.ibm.com&lt;/Sip&gt;
  &lt;/Dial&gt;
&lt;/Response&gt;
```

Let me know if that helps at all.

  [1]: https://www.twilio.com/docs/voice/twiml
  [2]: https://www.twilio.com/docs/voice/twiml/dial
  [3]: https://www.twilio.com/docs/voice/twiml/sip

